# gitleaks false-positive baseline.
#
# gitleaks ignores findings by FINGERPRINT (not by pattern). A fingerprint looks like:
#   <commit-sha>:<file-path>:<rule-id>:<line-number>
# It is printed in gitleaks' report/output for each finding.
#
# As of 2026-07-03, `gitleaks detect` over the full history reports NO leaks, so this
# baseline is intentionally empty. When a confirmed false positive appears (e.g. a test
# fixture or example value), paste its fingerprint on its own line below to suppress it.
# Do NOT suppress a real secret - rotate it, then purge it from history instead.
#
# Example (commented out):
# 0a1b2c3d4e5f6a7b8c9d:tests/fixtures/sample.env:generic-api-key:12
